Nov 11 2009 	Best budget hotel in London	We stayed at this hotel in one of their quad rooms, It was right at the top of the hotel so consequently a bit of walk with cases, however once there we were pleasantly surprised by the size of the room which was more than adequate for a family of four. The en suite bathroom was very clean as was the bedroom itself. Towels and shower freebies were changed or renewed daily. As was the tea/coffee/hot chocolate making facilities (we used our bottled water in the kettle for ease). The beds were very comfortable and sheets immaculate.The breakfast is excellent. To start there is a buffet table of cereals, fruit, yoghurt, tinned fruit, pastries etc followed by a full english breakfast or scrambled eggs with smoked salmon. The waitress serves as much toast and tea and coffee that you want. It must be the best breakfast in the whole of London. The staff are friendly and helpful, they let us leave our luggage free of charge on the last day so we could spend all day in London before having to catch our evening train.We would not hesitate to recommend this hotel to any family, it is very central in what appears to be a safe environment, there are plenty of buses and Russell Square Tube Station really is only a short walk.	
Nov 10 2009 	Ideal quiet base	I have stayed in this hotel about 10 times now, sometimes on my own, and sometimes with my partner, and I am very glad to have found it. I have stayed in some other really terrible hotels around Russell Square, and worse near King's Cross, and this is an oasis. The breakfast is a full English, and for vegetarians, my partner, they do mushrooms, and are very friendly about it, served to your table - not a buffet - along with other cakes and cereal etc. Beware of room number 1 because that is by the kitchen noise! and if you want a quiet room then you should as for one at the back of the hotel, single or double, on the first or second floor. Then you will be ok. Perhaps if there was a really good deal and I wanted a lie in then I would risk another hotel round this area, but for the purposes of somewhere safe, clean and friendly this is really ideal.	
