Jan 23 2009 	A delightful hotel in a great location!	My son was doing a semester abroad, so my brother-in-law and I went to visit him for a week in November. We had two single rooms at the Thanet Hotel, and it was absolutely perfect for us. The owners are very welcoming and accommodating, the breakfast was good and more than ample, the rooms were clean and well-appointed, the bathrooms were spotless, and the room rates are very reasonable, especially for London. We had adjacent rooms on the second floor, and in both of our rooms, the bathrooms were relatively new, and fully tiled, with really great water pressure so you can have a good hot shower. There was a small but new television in each room, too.I'll also note what some people might consider drawbacks, but if these things put you off, you probably shouldn't go to London at all. The hotel has no elevator, the rooms are small, and although Bedford Place is a relatively quiet street and the Thanet therefore one of the more quiet hotels in London, you can stil hear street noise in your room.Nevertheless, I highly recommend it. It's a very short (two or three block) walk to two Tube stops: Russell Square and High Holborn, and you can get just about anywhere from either of them. (In fact, you can take the Piccadilly Line from Heathrow directly to Russell Square, about a 50 minute ride, then walk a few blocks to the hotel, and save yourself a ton of money over the alternatives. Just be warned: you'll have to climb about twelve stairs to get out of the Russell Square station, after having taken an elevator from the platform, so if you have a lot of luggage, that could be difficult.) A bus also stops on Bedford Place, though I am not sure where it was going, and there are other bus stops nearby. And you can always catch a cab in the area.I have been to London six or eight times, and stayed in a different hotel each time, but from now on, I stay at the Thanet. I really liked it that much.	
