Apr 1 2005	Great location - good value	Can only agree with previous reviews about this hotel's great location (minutes from the British Museum) and only £4.00 taxi fare from Euston. (I hate using the Tube - particularly the lift at Russell Square!) There is also a good connection of buses just around the corner but most areas convenient to walk to.The rooms are very clean and tidy and nice en-suite facilities The staff are most helpful and willing to advise on any travel issues etc.The breakfast is more than substantial with a choice of cereals and fresh fruit followed by an excellent choice of cooked breakfast to set you on your way.My one small complaint would be the noise from the traffic which did disturb us. Other reviews mentioned that this was a quiet street but we did see a 'diversion sign' which may have accounted for the excessive traffic noise we experienced. Neverthelesss, great value for money - enjoy your stay.	
