Aug 31 2004	A Great B	My husband and I and our two teenage sons stayed at the Thanet for 7 nights in July. We were given a large room on the first floor with a double bed and two twin beds which was perfect since our sons like to have their own beds. The location is great and easily accessible from both Holborn and Russell tube stations, as well as bus stops. The breakfast is outstanding with a buffet of fruit, cereal, muffins, juice, and an ordered breakfast of full English, hot oatmeal, or smoked salmon. There's also tea, instant coffee, and hot chocolate available in the room, with cookies. Our only complaint (and it was a very small one) was that the person who serviced our room could never seem to remember to leave 4 towels and 4 cookies. The person manning the front desk was always VERY helpful. As an aside, consider going on a day trip to Bath with Premier Tours. They stop at Stonehenge like the other day trips to Bath, but they stop after hours so that you're allowed to touch the stones. It was awesome!	
