Jul 22 2004	Stay here! You won't be disappointed	My husband and I stayed at the Thanet for four nights in June. We loved everything about the place: location, staff (Albert is wonderful!) the breakfast, many affordable restaurants around the area, post office, bureau de change, internet kiosk, British Museum next street over, and the short walk through Russell Square to the tube station was a nice way to start the day. If you are coming from Heathrow, you can take the tube all the way there without switching lines with all your luggage. While the convenience of all the surrounding amenities was nice, it was even better that the hotel is not on a busy road so we always slept peacefully. The room was surprisingly large-I felt like I was at Grandma's house. We'll definitely stay there again.	
Jun 29 2004	Nice place nice people great location	Stayed here on March 27th 2004 for one night just to hit the London nightlife and this was a great place to stay. Was recommended to try the Thanet Hotel after reading the Which? Reports review of B&amp;B’s in London. This one came out favourably as good value for money and a clean and comfortable place to stay the night. I emailed the Landlord to organise this and he was very helpful in arranging my booking. When I arrived I was greeted by the Landlord and given my key for our room, which was right at the top of the house but a rather cosy little room. The beds were comfy and the bathroom was nicely done in a modern way with mosaic tiles and a small shower which made a change from the usual old baths with rusty shower heads you get in most B&amp;B’s and hotels! Although the décor in the room wasn’t up to date and could do with a makeover badly, it served its purpose for a nights stay and we weren’t in the room much to worry about it. We had the full English breakfast the next day which was really nice and there was plenty of tea and coffee, juice, toast and cereal if you fancied it.Overall I would really recommend this B&amp;B as it was only 10 minutes walk from Holborn tube station (Russell Square station seemed closer – only five minutes walk) and 10 minutes walk to Tottenham Court Road. A safe and comfortable place to stay, a great value for money. We are staying there again this Saturday 3rd July too!	
